api_list.name: TIME_SERIES_DAILY
api_list.description: This API returns daily time series (date, daily open, daily high, daily low, daily close, daily volume) of the global equity specified, covering 20+ years of historical data.

required_parameters.name: function
required_parameters.description: The time series of your choice.

required_parameters.name: symbol
required_parameters.description: The name of the equity of your choice.

optional_parameters.name: datatype
optional_parameters.description: Strings json and csv are accepted with the following specifications: json returns the daily time series in JSON format; csv returns the time series as a CSV (comma separated value) file.

optional_parameters.name: outputsize
optional_parameters.description: Strings compact and full are accepted with the following specifications: compact returns only the latest 100 data points; full returns the full-length time series of 20+ years of historical data. The \\\"compact\\\" option is recommended if you would like to reduce the data size of each API call.

api_list.name: Search Endpoint
api_list.description: Looking for some specific symbols or companies? We've got you covered! The Search Endpoint returns the best-matching symbols and market information based on keywords of your choice. The search results also contain match scores that provide you with the full flexibility to develop your own search and filtering logic.

required_parameters.name: keywords
required_parameters.description: A text string of your choice.

required_parameters.name: function
required_parameters.description: The API function of your choice.

optional_parameters.name: datatype
optional_parameters.description: Strings json and csv are accepted with the following specifications: json returns the search results in JSON format; csv returns the search results as a CSV (comma separated value) file.

api_list.name: DIGITAL_CURRENCY_WEEKLY
api_list.description: This API returns the weekly historical time series for a digital currency (e.g., BTC) traded on a specific market (e.g., CNY/Chinese Yuan), refreshed daily at midnight (UTC). Prices and volumes are quoted in both the market-specific currency and USD.

required_parameters.name: market
required_parameters.description: The exchange market of your choice. It can be any of the market in the market list. For example: market=CNY.

required_parameters.name: function
required_parameters.description: The time series of your choice.

required_parameters.name: symbol
required_parameters.description: The digital/crypto currency of your choice. It can be any of the currencies in the digital currency list. For example: symbol=BTC.

api_list.name: Technical Indicators
api_list.description: For more information on how to build all the different technical indicators there are, [please visit here](https://www.alphavantage.co/documentation/#technical-indicators).

required_parameters.name: time_period
required_parameters.description: Number of data points used to calculate each moving average value. Positive integers are accepted (e.g., time_period=60, time_period=200)

required_parameters.name: interval
required_parameters.description: Time interval between two consecutive data points in the time series. The following values are supported: 1min, 5min, 15min, 30min, 60min, daily, weekly, monthly

required_parameters.name: series_type
required_parameters.description: The desired price type in the time series. Four types are supported: close, open, high, low

required_parameters.name: function
required_parameters.description: The technical indicator of your choice. In this case, function=SMA

required_parameters.name: symbol
required_parameters.description: The name of the security of your choice. For example: symbol=MSFT

optional_parameters.name: datatype
optional_parameters.description: By default, datatype=json. Strings json and csv are accepted with the following specifications: json returns the daily time series in JSON format; csv returns the time series as a CSV (comma separated value) file.

api_list.name: CURRENCY_EXCHANGE_RATE (Crypto)
api_list.description: This API returns the realtime exchange rate for any pair of digital currency (e.g., Bitcoin) or physical currency (e.g., USD).

required_parameters.name: from_currency
required_parameters.description: The cryptocurrency you want to convert from

required_parameters.name: function
required_parameters.description: The function of your choice. (In this case CURRENCY_EXCHANGE_RATE)

required_parameters.name: to_currency
required_parameters.description: The currency you want to convert to

api_list.name: FX_INTRADAY
api_list.description: This API returns intraday time series (timestamp, open, high, low, close) of the FX currency pair specified, updated realtime.

required_parameters.name: function
required_parameters.description: The time series of your choice.

required_parameters.name: interval
required_parameters.description: Time interval between two consecutive data points in the time series. The following values are supported: 1min, 5min, 15min, 30min, 60min

required_parameters.name: to_symbol
required_parameters.description: A three-letter symbol from the forex currency list. For example: to_symbol=USD

required_parameters.name: from_symbol
required_parameters.description: A three-letter symbol from the forex currency list. For example: from_symbol=EUR

optional_parameters.name: datatype
optional_parameters.description: By default, datatype=json. Strings json and csv are accepted with the following specifications: json returns the intraday time series in JSON format; csv returns the time series as a CSV (comma separated value) file.

optional_parameters.name: outputsize
optional_parameters.description: By default, outputsize=compact. Strings compact and full are accepted with the following specifications: compact returns only the latest 100 data points in the intraday time series; full returns the full-length intraday time series. The "compact" option is recommended if you would like to reduce the data size of each API call.

required_parameters.description: A three-letter symbol from the forex currency list. For example: to_symbol=USD

optional_parameters.name: datatype
optional_parameters.description: By default, datatype=json. Strings json and csv are accepted with the following specifications: json returns the weekly time series in JSON format; csv returns the time series as a CSV (comma separated value) file.
